<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1340&amp;p=11663#p11663"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Creating Original Graphics Using TLP and YY-CHR ???]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1340&amp;p=11663#p11663"><![CDATA[
You can make up to four palettes for the background and four palettes for sprites. All eight palettes must share the same color 0. The program can rewrite any or all of the palette at any time by loading a new palette into PPU memory $3F00-$3F1F.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Fri Apr 07, 2006 2:14 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
