<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1340&amp;p=11654#p11654"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Creating Original Graphics Using TLP and YY-CHR ???]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1340&amp;p=11654#p11654"><![CDATA[
Foreseeing the problems with getting the original MS-DOS versions of SnowBro's Tile Layer and NSA to work on a machine running NT (that is, win2k/winxp/vista), I wrote my own clones of the programs, called 8TED and 8name respectively. See <a href="http://www.pineight.com/pc/#ted" class="postlink">Pin Eight NES Tools</a>. In 8TED, if you try to open a nonexistent file, it will create a new file of 8192 bytes, and then you can press Ctrl+R to resize it.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Fri Apr 07, 2006 12:43 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
