<title type="html"><![CDATA[Creating Original Graphics Using TLP and YY-CHR ???]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1340&amp;p=11644#p11644"><![CDATA[
Open up a hex editor, make a new file and fill it with 8k ($2000) bytes of 00s<br /><br />Or ... if you don't have a hex editor, you can make a .txt file in notepad that's 8k (fill it with spaces or something), and rename the extension to .chr  (of course if you do this, it'll have garbage graphics instead of blank graphics, but same difference).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=33">Disch</a> — Fri Apr 07, 2006 5:56 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
